 be aware that the duration of the audiobook generation process may vary from a few hours to a few days,<br>depending on the length of the audiobook.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><br>once your audiobook has been generated,<br>You will receive an email notification that your audiobook is ready for proof hearing.<br>at this point, you can proceed to step 2.<br><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><br><strong>Step 2: <\/strong>Editing the Audiobook.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>when you&#8217;re ready, click &#8216;Continue&#8217;, and a new window will appear, displaying the entire book.<br><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>From this point onward, any changes you make will be automatically saved in spines.<br><br>Now, let&#8217;s explore the array of tools at your disposal for effectively proof-hearing your book.<br><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Select any sentence and click &#8216;Play&#8217; to hear it.<br><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>You can also select specific words and modify their pronunciation, even if there are spelling errors.<br><br>The key is to ensure the words are pronounced correctly.&nbsp;<br><br>By making changes and iterations, you can refine the pronunciation until it sounds correct. This way, you have control over how the words are pronounced in the AI-generated voice.<br><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><br>One way to do this is to write the frenetic pronunciation of the word<br><br>bonus tip:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>you can always google search the frenetic pronunciation of any word.<br>This can provide you with valuable suggestions to ensure accurate pronunciation in the AI-generated voice.<br><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>If you want the changes made to a specific word to apply throughout the entire text, click the &#8216;Find and Replace Everywhere in the Book&#8217; button.&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><br>You can give emphasis to individual words or multiple words by clicking on the word and pressing &#8216;Apply&#8217;.<br><br>To select multiple words, hold down &#8216;Shift.&#8217;<br>Similarly, you can select paragraphs or multiple paragraphs by pressing and holding &#8216;Shift&#8217;.<br><br>Adjust the speed, volume, language, and even the voice for each selection.<br><br>If your story involves multiple characters and you want each one to have their own voice, there are a couple of ways to achieve this.<br><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>One way is to change the voice sentence by sentence, assigning a specific voice to each character as needed throughout the narrative.<br><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Alternatively, you can create new roles and assign different voices to each role.<br><br>This approach simplifies the process of incorporating multiple voices into the story, as you can easily switch between the assigned voices for each character.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>If you need to split paragraphs into multiple sections, click the &#8216;Cut &amp; Edit&#8217; button.<br>Here, you can select a part of the audio to create longer pauses or change voices in the middle.<br><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>When you navigate between paragraphs, chapters, and subtitles,<br>you can easily adjust the pause duration to your preference.<br>This adjustment can be applied to the entire book.<br><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>In the lower section, you can play the full audiobook,<br>adjust the playback speed and volume,<br>and move between the paragraphs.<br><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>By right-clicking on any word, you can set the text as normal text, chapter title, chapter subtitle, or subtitle.<br>Each paragraph type has different lengths for pauses.<br><br>Please note that once you click the &#8216;Finish Editing&#8217; button located in the upper left corner, you will receive the final version of your edited audiobook.<br><br>It&#8217;s important to ensure that the entire audiobook is complete and set up correctly before proceeding,<br>as you won&#8217;t be able to make any further changes after this point.<br><br>Take the time to review and confirm that everything is in order before finalizing the process.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>when you are ready &#8211; click on \u2018Finish Editing\u2019.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"searchtags h